Third body perturbations
The third-body potential implemented in PlanODyn is expanded in powers of the parallactic factor (a/rb) as in [34, 15], where rb is the geocentric distance of the perturber. Terms up to the fourth order (P2, P3, P4) in the expansion are retained for both the Sun and the Moon.
