Earth’s general precession
The long-term contribution of Earth’s general precession is described in detail in Appendix B. The perturbing function yields:
Rprec = √a (1 − e2) μ⊕(Px sin(i) sin(Ω) − Py sin(i) cos(Ω) + Pz cos(i))
where P = (Px, Py, Pz) is the angular velocity of a precessing geocentric equatorial frame relative to an inertial (i.e. J2000).
